    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>/pages/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/pages/about/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I’m a backend engineer focused on application security and system resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I care about failure modes, blast radius, and how small decisions turn into large security problems. My background includes security tooling, cloud infrastructure, and building internal systems in constrained, real-world environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This site is a working notebook. I use it to publish security experiments, AWS hardening notes, and practical breakdowns of how systems fail and how to make them harder to misuse.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
